Done! The API is ready to run. Key features implemented:

**All in one file** (`main.go`):
- ✅ **CRUD endpoints**: GET/POST/PUT/DELETE for `/users` and `/users/{id}`
- ✅ **Auth middleware**: Requires `Authorization: Bearer secret-token`
- ✅ **Rate limiting**: 100 requests per IP per minute
- ✅ **Cache**: In-memory lookup cache by user ID (uses `cacheMu` from template)
- ✅ **JSON everywhere**: All responses are JSON-encoded
- ✅ **Standard library only**: Uses only `net/http`, `encoding/json`, `sync`, and `time`
- ✅ **Runnable**: `go run .` on port 8080

**Test it with**:
```bash
go run .

# In another terminal, create a user
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/users \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer secret-token" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name":"Alice","email":"alice@example.com"}'

# Get all users
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer secret-token" http://localhost:8080/users

# Get user by ID
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer secret-token" http://localhost:8080/users/1

# Update user
curl -X PUT http://localhost:8080/users/1 \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer secret-token" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name":"Alice Smith"}'

# Delete user
curl -X DELETE -H "Authorization: Bearer secret-token" http://localhost:8080/users/1
```
